headline: Consolidated Edison Q1 Earnings Miss Estimates, Revenues Rise Y/Y
summary: ED's first-quarter earnings miss estimates, and revenues grow 12.1% year over year. The company's operating income rises during the same period.

headline: This Is the Quintessential Energy Stock to Buy for the Coming Power Surge
summary: The U.S. will need to add an estimated 450 gigawatts of power-generating capacity by 2030.  Given the limitations of gas and nuclear, renewables will play a leading role in the near term.  NextEra Energy is in an ideal position to meet the country's power needs.
